{{calligraphy-stub}}

The article provides details and data regarding the '''geographical''' '''distribution of all Dutch speakers''', regardless of the legislative status of the countries where it's spoken. The Dutch language is the dominant language of the [[Netherlands]], in the [[Flanders]] and in [[Suriname]]. It's also spoken in minority areas through Europe and in many immigrant communities in all over the world. [[Afrikaans]], even if it's a daughter language of Dutch it's regarded as a separate language and will not be analyzed in this article.
